that I failed to say about Korea that had an effect 
on my career was that I had developed a back

35:28.559 --> 35:42.339
problem, a herniated disc. I don't know what 
caused it. It just happened. Spinal disc? Yeah.

35:45.965 --> 35:50.131
And so I spent considerable time, about three 
weeks, in the hospital. And it results with that

35:51.894 --> 35:56.220
physical problem. In Korea? You were in the 
hospital in Korea? Yeah. If I was in the States, I'd

36:01.391 --> 36:11.827
probably go to Walton Reed where they had the 
surgery, but I wanted to finish my tour in Korea

36:01.391 --> 36:11.827
because this happened halfway through the tour. 
